lign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utechiex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>techiex</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/9/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>11:19:13 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.lavadragon.com/tech.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Balance? Hah!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The way I see it:<br>
I did do alot of dmg on raid, Then Velious came out, Now I waste all my mana on 1 mob, Just to see the group with a monk grab the kill everytime.<br>
<br>
It use to be that if I used 50% of my mana I was sured the kill, Not in today's game, it wont happen no matter how hard you try, I was a wizard, Now I'm a monk.<br>
<br>
Now I'm a monk and my group gets all the kills, But I miss playing my wizard, Verant decides to &quot;nerf&quot; clerics to bring melee effiency down, Melee's find more and better weapons, melee effiency goes up and not down.<br>
<br>
If Verant had any type of friggin clue already, they should inherit what past games have done ( Diablo I / II, D&amp;D, etc.. ). What do I mean ? Well, I mean give us casters items that increase our dmg. How so ? Well, lets take Diablo for example... Sorceress gets items that increase dmg output on certain spells. Jeese, last time I checked Everquest is suppose to be a D&amp;D based game. &lt; pulls out the old board game &gt; LOOK VERANT LOOK ON THE CARDS - IT ADDS MORE DMG TO CERTAIN SPELLS. Why is Verant so blind to this fact ? Why do they constantly ignore it ? And if they thought about adding this in the game, how would it effect melee's ? Well, my guess is melee's would moan and bitch about it being unbalancing. &lt; gets out everquest manual &gt; &lt; looks up warrior's, &quot;A Warrior is a master of armed combat, in all its forms. He's at home on the battlefield, and is TRAINED TO TAKE AS MUCH PUNISHMENT...&quot; &gt; ok, EQ Manual says: Warrior's are Punching bags &lt; looks up wizard's, &quot;The Wizard is a seeker of knowledge, and her life is spent focusing on this goal. She uses powerful spells to see things from afar and transport them between places. A thirst for arcane knowledge has made her a master of defense as well as an offensive force of destruction.&quot; - Reality check: &quot;master of defense&quot; - ok, I played a wizard to 56, someone please tell me what in the hell defense we got while we sit on our butts trying to gain mana ? Oh wait, I know, defense = the cleric that got the aggro for us /nod sure sure thats it !<br>
&quot;an offensive force of destruction&quot; - Yep, we are the masters of DD, we do about 5 spells, then oom, sit to med, by the time we are fom the mob has fully regen'd... Nice One ! ps. By the time we are FoM is usually when we magically appear at our bind spots with all are gear left in the &quot;other&quot; zone.<br>
<br>
To accuratly fix a FEW problems with wizards, I say:<br>
1 - Give Wizards higher AC than any other casting class. We should get about 200 to 300 more ac than a mag / nec / enc by lvl 60. Lets think about this, we are the so called master of defense, yet we really have no defense, no pets, every, EVERY other INT casting class has a pet ( by pet, I mean one that doesn't POOF after the mob is dead ). Mages get self buffs that give AC and HP Regen PLUS the same exact buffs we get for. Enchanters get AC buffs, better runes, plus the same buffs we get. Necro's get a crapload of buffs, plus they regen mana faster than c2 - hell I'll gladly eschange my hp for mana any day !. Wizards get the same shield buffs every other int caster class gets plus a rip off of a few enchanter spells that a just cheap rune spells. Least with higher AC we will have SOME defense, and might not get blown over in 5 hits.<br>
<br>
2 - Give us a spell that convert's hp to mana, I dont care if it has to take a component, gimme the friggin spell you tight wads, maybe I'll be useful in Velious. /dream<br>
<br>
3 - Give Wizards a new nuke for 54 to 56 lvl range. Have you noticed the sudden increase in lvl 60 spells ? Wow, I think verant employee's are saying to themselfs, &quot;Hey wizards are complaining about how un-balanced they are, what should we do ? employee1 says, I got it, lets give them more lvl 60 spells to drool about ! And lets make the spells look good and have cool names, but in all actuality they suck !&quot;<br>
<br>
Ok, Enough of my rambling about how verant told us to bend over and &quot;take one for the team&quot; /fu, I will go back to playing my lvl 45 monk, I need to get him out of hell. <br>
Peace...<br>
